It's all talking about seedtime and harvest. But the body of Christ doesn't want to talk about it. We throw it away.

01:24:39.005 --> 01:24:45.765
'Oh, we don't want to talk about it because the love of money is the root of all evil.'But most of you can't even make your rent.

01:24:45.766 --> 01:24:51.566
Most of you can't pay your car payment and the repo man is coming.

01:24:51.567 --> 01:24:58.794
How much can we be a light to those around us if we have a little extra to be able to say, 'Listen, you need some help for your bill, sir?

01:24:58.795 --> 01:25:09.683
I got it in my account. Let me help you out. I want to tell you about Jesus this holiday season. You don't have Christmas for your kids?

01:25:09.684 --> 01:25:17.319
Let me give you a couple extra hundred dollars here, and you can bless your kids, and let me show you about Jesus and how much He loves you'?

01:25:17.320 --> 01:25:23.142
But most of us in the body of Christ are going, 'Man, I don't know.

01:25:23.143 --> 01:25:34.431
I don't want to talk about the prosperity gospel.'I'm upset because we see somebody have a big old house in Louisiana or wherever and you get upset about it, but you don't know the seeds they sowed to get it.

01:25:34.432 --> 01:25:37.899
You don't know what they had to get it, and most people persecute them because they have it.

01:25:37.900 --> 01:25:43.663
But I'm going to tell you this: the Bible works. The Word will work if you work it.

01:25:43.664 --> 01:25:54.488
And I'm telling you, ladies and gentlemen, I'm a believer that believes in Deuteronomy 28. People get upset at me about that. I don't care.

01:25:54.489 --> 01:26:03.333
I'm believing God that He's going to give me a creative idea to get wealth, and that XRP and these things that I'm praying over will take off like a rocket in the days ahead.

01:26:03.334 --> 01:26:14.079
It's my opinion and I'm believing for it. Not financial advice—I have to say it every time.

01:26:14.080 --> 01:26:25.376
I just believe in this end-time wealth transfer. Father, I thank You, Lord, for every single person here.

01:26:25.377 --> 01:26:34.079
I bless them. I bless their marriages. I thank You, Father, that You're the God who restores what the cankerworm has eaten.

01:26:34.080 --> 01:26:41.211
That their marriages will be good; their love life will be even better. That they'll dance and have fun as a married couple.

01:26:41.212 --> 01:26:51.016
They'll sing songs together, hold hands, walk in the park, go look at the lake, feed the ducks—whatever it takes to make their marriage happy again.

01:26:51.017 --> 01:27:05.763
Go on a date, make things spicy. Let's have a good marriage. Father, I thank You, Lord, that You restore back and that You want our marriages to be happy.

01:27:05.764 --> 01:27:12.388
You want our children to see that mommy and daddy love each other, that there's not bickering and strife in the home.

01:27:12.389 --> 01:27:26.883
Instead of walking around asking if mommy and daddy are going to get a divorce, they see mommy and daddy and go, 'I want to mirror my marriage after mommy and daddy because they're my heroes.

01:27:26.884 --> 01:27:37.898
I love the Jesus in them.'You display Jesus to your children through how you act, by treating each other well.

01:27:37.899 --> 01:27:45.142
How much do you show your wife love, sir? How much do you honor your husbands, wives?

01:27:45.143 --> 01:27:50.270
Do you love them? Do you honor them? Do you treat them with respect?

01:27:50.271 --> 01:27:54.548
Do you hold their hands? Do you act like you're dating still?

01:27:54.549 --> 01:27:59.914
Or has it become dry, and you wake up and don't even want to lie next to them in the bed?

01:27:59.915 --> 01:28:03.839
You sit on the couch, and you're on one end and the other's on the other end.

01:28:03.840 --> 01:28:07.999
You're watching TV together and you don't even know they're in the room.

01:28:08.000 --> 01:28:17.999
Your love life is stagnant. Your marriage bed is dried and old.

01:28:18.000 --> 01:28:30.262
It's time to renew the flame that you once had. Renew the flame in your marriages.

01:28:30.263 --> 01:28:38.188
Make marriage great again. And those that are believing for a spouse: make your list.

01:28:38.189 --> 01:28:47.325
Write the vision down and make it plain. Take it to God with communion and tell the Lord, 'I'm believing God for a spouse. I want a godly man.

01:28:47.326 --> 01:28:59.333
I want a godly woman.'And in 2026, Father, I thank You that You're bringing my Esther, or my Boaz, or whatever I'm believing for.

01:28:59.334 --> 01:29:10.279
Try to always bring a Bible character into it. I don't know. Believe God. Write the vision down.

01:29:10.280 --> 01:29:20.544
I'm believing for a brown-eyed, brown-haired, porcelain-skinned woman. I don't know.

01:29:20.545 --> 01:29:36.055
Whatever you're believing for, I'm believing God for a man that will provide, will have a job, be steady, and not be a lazy sack of potatoes sitting on the couch and not wanting to help provide for me—one who will get off his lazy butt and go get a job.

01:29:36.056 --> 01:29:47.102
I believe for a man that will provide and help out around the house, who will help me do laundry and tell me I'm pretty every once in a while.

01:29:47.103 --> 01:29:55.818
My man's going to turn around and stop being some booze-sipping, porn-looking, whatever he's doing. Bad man.

01:29:55.819 --> 01:30:03.119
I'm believing God for a man that's going to be faithful to me with his eyes and faithful in taking me to church on Sundays.

01:30:03.120 --> 01:30:09.438
Believe God, ladies. Believe God. Men, I'm believing God my wife will cook me dinner.

01:30:09.439 --> 01:30:16.163
I'm believing God for this. I'm believing for that. I don't know what you want in a woman; I have what I'm believing for.

01:30:16.164 --> 01:30:27.519
Everybody has a heart's desire for something. But don't complain about the 80% that you do have and complain about the 20% that you don't.

01:30:27.520 --> 01:30:35.767
The grass isn't greener on the other side. She doesn't meet all my needs? There's nobody 100%. I don't care who you are.

01:30:35.768 --> 01:30:39.029
There's no woman that's ever going to be 100% of what you're looking for.

01:30:39.030 --> 01:30:45.927
I've never seen it. There's not a man that's 100%. So, don't be too picky with what you have in front of you.

01:30:45.928 --> 01:30:55.999
Well, he does have a potbelly. I was hoping for a six-pack, but he meets all the other criteria.

01:30:56.000 --> 01:31:01.895
Well, are you the hundred percent? Probably not, sister clipboard.

01:31:01.896 --> 01:31:10.316
You're probably not, just being real with you. Your breath stinks when you wake up too, just like his.

01:31:10.317 --> 01:31:21.439
But you've got to be real with folks. And I'm thinking it's sad about some of these people that say, 'I'm single. I'm believing God for a perfect man.'Well, good luck.

01:31:21.440 --> 01:31:35.999
I saw a sign that had a skeleton on a park bench and she had a sign in her hands that said, 'I'm waiting for a perfect man.'She'd been waiting for a long time and you aren't going to find him.

01:31:36.000 --> 01:31:46.638
She died waiting. But believe God for big. Don't settle. Believe God for big and don't be unequally yoked.

01:31:46.639 --> 01:31:55.925
Don't find somebody that is unequally yoked and not saved and then say, 'I want to get him saved and then we're going to get married and we're going to have a happy life together.'No, you're in trouble.

01:31:55.926 --> 01:32:09.091
The Bible says, 'Do not be unequally yoked with unbelievers.'Find you a believing believer and don't settle for an unbeliever and say, 'Well, I'm going to get him saved after he gets here,'or, 'I'm going to get her saved.'Boy, she's fine.

01:32:09.092 --> 01:32:13.434
Boy, she's fine. We're going to get her saved. We'll take her to church and she's going to get baptized in the Holy Ghost.

01:32:13.435 --> 01:32:19.194
And guess what? She's a Jezebel. Don't settle for a Jezebel that's going to take you down.

01:32:19.195 --> 01:32:40.079
Because the Lord said, 'Many of my men of God have married Jezebels and they've attached their neck to a rock, and they'll never take off like a rocket as they should because they married a Jezebel.'I don't know why I'm saying all this, but it's for somebody.

01:32:40.080 --> 01:32:49.359
Believe God in 2026. Write your vision down. What are you believing for?

01:32:49.360 --> 01:32:52.895
Have your list, top five. 'Lord, I'm believing for a new house.

01:32:52.896 --> 01:32:55.627
I'm believing for a new car.'Like Diana and I, we believe for a car.

01:32:55.628 --> 01:33:01.443
Write down your vision. 'Father, I call this car. I'm believing for this car.

01:33:01.444 --> 01:33:10.133
I want a brand-new SUV, white, black, whatever.'Have your list down and put the vision down.

01:33:10.134 --> 01:33:20.029
Write it down and put scripture behind it. Sew a seed at the church. If you have a need, sew a seed.

01:33:20.030 --> 01:33:26.140
Take your seed to the church and do that and continue, and then believe and use scripture.

01:33:26.141 --> 01:33:31.464
Put it on the mirror. Keep the vision. I drive around and look for vision. I put it inside of me.

01:33:31.465 --> 01:33:37.634
And the bigger that vision gets on the inside of me, the more it changes me.

01:33:37.635 --> 01:33:52.770
You have to have an inward image of it. So there you go. Does it help anybody?

01:33:52.771 --> 01:33:56.152
Maybe it does, maybe it doesn't. But you've got to have a vision for something.

01:33:56.153 --> 01:34:03.472
If you're believing God for a vision... I prayed for these people down in Chile, South America somewhere.

01:34:03.473 --> 01:34:05.122
They needed a medical business. I prayed over that for them.

01:34:05.123 --> 01:34:11.873
They were a blessing to us. Was it Brazil or something? A Brazil medical center.

01:34:11.874 --> 01:34:16.331
And it was a wall. My goodness. We prayed for that over a year and they finally got their breakthrough.

01:34:16.332 --> 01:34:20.879
It's a surgery center and the government was coming against them and the Lord had me intercede for that.

01:34:20.880 --> 01:34:28.712
I prayed for that breakthrough because they're going to be a blessing to this surgical center and prayed for their daughter not to have seizures anymore.

01:34:28.713 --> 01:34:34.450
They had to start with something and they believed God. They set their faith out there to believe for it and God came through.

01:34:34.451 --> 01:34:39.468
Now they're going to help people with all this stuff. I believe they're a blessing to ministries.

01:34:39.469 --> 01:34:43.316
I know that it's not always to hoard up for ourselves. We're helping people.

01:34:43.317 --> 01:34:53.563
So that's what I try to tell you and encourage you: believe God for big, but not just believe God that you can have a Dodge Viper or a Corvette or whatever you want.

01:34:53.564 --> 01:35:05.471
Believe God for that and believe God for extra, for more. It's not wrong to have good things, but as long as the things don't have you.

01:35:05.472 --> 01:35:10.474
That's what I do at the beginning of every year. I believe God for a vacation.

01:35:10.475 --> 01:35:14.652
So I sew my seed and believe God for a vacation. Where do you want to go?

01:35:14.653 --> 01:35:18.844
You may not make it there that year. 'I'm believing God to go to Hawaii.'Let's go to Hawaii.

01:35:18.845 --> 01:35:24.848
Let's believe God for big. So you sew your seed at the church, maybe 25 or 30 bucks.

01:35:24.849 --> 01:35:28.095
You believe God for extra money. You say, 'Hey, let's believe God.

01:35:28.096 --> 01:35:34.967
We got one plane ticket. We may have a hotel room for a day.'You start somewhere.

01:35:34.968 --> 01:35:40.365
You may make it to California and that might be fun, but one day you make it to Hawaii.

01:35:40.366 --> 01:35:47.836
You've got to start where your faith's at. I talked to a young man today about air conditioning.

01:35:47.837 --> 01:36:00.311
I told him, 'You've got to learn how to believe God for $5 before you can believe God for a million.'And most people's faith is just at the $5.

01:36:00.312 --> 01:36:06.132
Don't be weary in well-doing and don't look at small beginnings as bad. You've got to start somewhere.

01:36:06.133 --> 01:36:12.872
Believe God for a dollar and say, 'God, I thank you for that dollar.'It's a consecutive dollar every single day.

01:36:12.873 --> 01:36:15.966
You might have $30 at the end of the month. And you go, 'Well, glory to God.

01:36:15.967 --> 01:36:22.758
I got my $30. You provided for me.'At least you started somewhere.

01:36:22.759 --> 01:36:30.479
Don't despise small beginnings. Be faithful with little and He'll make you ruler over much.

01:36:30.480 --> 01:36:44.711
I believe it. But start somewhere, whether it's a bicycle or a brand-new truck.

01:36:44.712 --> 01:36:51.988
So, that's my two cents. It's all word-based. It's not just me.

01:36:51.989 --> 01:36:57.134
I'm tired, so I'm going to go. I think that's good enough tonight. What do you think?

01:36:57.135 --> 01:37:03.434
It's a different kind of video, but that's just where I was tonight after the Christmas party.

01:37:03.435 --> 01:37:13.200
I appreciate y'all praying for me. We'll be back again tomorrow and we'll make another video for you. As always, I know it's late. God bless you all.

01:37:13.201 --> 01:37:20.659
If you could like, subscribe, click the notification bell, and click the thumbs-up button—all the things you can do to help me.

01:37:20.660 --> 01:37:24.648
We'll see what the Lord shows us next time. We appreciate you.

01:37:24.649 --> 01:37:31.690
Remember, put a smile on your face and a song in your heart. Jesus loves you and we love you.

01:37:31.691 --> 01:37:38.719
God bless you all and we'll see you again tomorrow. Bye-bye.

